1. Get-ChildItem -Force pages/PublicMenu | Select-Object Name,Length,LastWriteTime

2. (Get-Content pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx | Measure-Object -Line).Lines

3. $path='pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx'; $start=1595; $end=1715; $i=0; Get-Content $path | ForEach-Object { $i++; if ($i -ge $start -and $i -le $end) { '{0,5}: {1}' -f $i, $_ } }

4. $path='pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx'; $start=3675; $end=3815; $i=0; Get-Content $path | ForEach-Object { $i++; if ($i -ge $start -and $i -le $end) { '{0,5}: {1}' -f $i, $_ } }

5. Select-String -Path 'pages/PublicMenu/BUGS.md','pages/PublicMenu/README.md' -Pattern 'PM-133|PM-134|PM-135|help drawer|Help Drawer|openHelpDrawer|Другое' -Context 2,4 | ForEach-Object { "`n>>> $($_.Path):$($_.LineNumber)`n$($_.Context.PreContext -join "`n")`n$($_.Line)`n$($_.Context.PostContext -join "`n")" }

6. Select-String -Path 'pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx' -Pattern 'Для запроса помощи выберите стол|helpSubmitError|active_request' -Context 1,2 | ForEach-Object { "`n>>> Line $($_.LineNumber)`n$($_.Context.PreContext -join "`n")`n$($_.Line)`n$($_.Context.PostContext -join "`n")" }

7. Select-String -Path 'pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx' -Pattern 'openHelpDrawer|setShowTableConfirmSheet|pushOverlay\(' -Context 2,3 | ForEach-Object { "`n>>> Line $($_.LineNumber)`n$($_.Context.PreContext -join "`n")`n$($_.Line)`n$($_.Context.PostContext -join "`n")" }

8. Select-String -Path 'pages/PublicMenu/README.md' -Pattern 'help|drawer|PM-133|PM-134|PM-135|Другое' -Context 1,2 | ForEach-Object { "`n>>> Line $($_.LineNumber)`n$($_.Context.PreContext -join "`n")`n$($_.Line)`n$($_.Context.PostContext -join "`n")" }

9. Get-Command codex | Select-Object Name,Source,Version

10. $path='pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx'
$snippet1 = (($lines = Get-Content $path)[1625..1704]) -join "`n"
$snippet2 = (($lines = Get-Content $path)[3697..3794]) -join "`n"
$prompt = @"
You are an independent code reviewer for MenuApp, a React/Base44 restaurant QR-menu app.

SCOPE LOCK:
- Review ONLY PM-133, PM-134, PM-135 in pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx.
- Do NOT report anything outside these fixes.
- Do NOT suggest changes to handleHelpFromCart.
- Do NOT change frozen UX items except the specific layout change for PM-134(c).

Task:
1. Review the proposed findings below against the code excerpts.
2. For each finding: APPROVE, REJECT, or IMPROVE.
3. Add any missed issue only if it is strictly inside PM-133/134/135 scope.
4. Be concise.

Format:
## Codex Patch Review: pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx
### Approved Findings
### Rejected Findings
### Improved Findings
### New Scoped Findings
### Summary

CODE EXCERPT A:
$snippet1

CODE EXCERPT B:
$snippet2

PROPOSED FINDINGS:
1. PM-133 / P1: openHelpDrawer() at lines 1655-1658 opens the help drawer unconditionally. It does not guard on currentTableId or redirect to setShowTableConfirmSheet(true), so hall users without a verified table still enter the help drawer and hit the in-drawer error path instead of the table-code sheet.
   Proposed fix: add `if (!currentTableId) { setShowTableConfirmSheet(true); return; }` at the top of openHelpDrawer and add currentTableId/setShowTableConfirmSheet to the dependency array.
2. PM-134(a) / P2: the "Другое" form at lines 3767-3787 stays mounted and relies on `overflow-hidden transition-all ... max-h-0 opacity-0`. That does not guarantee the textarea is absent from the DOM, matching the Android partial-visibility bug.
   Proposed fix: replace the collapsible div with conditional rendering `{showOtherForm && (...)}`.
3. PM-134(b) / P2: the textarea at lines 3769-3774 mounts without `autoFocus`, so tapping "Другое" will not automatically focus the field and open the mobile keyboard.
   Proposed fix: add `autoFocus` to the textarea once it is conditionally rendered.
4. PM-134(c) / P2: the submit button at lines 3776-3785 remains inside the same collapsible content block as the textarea. When the keyboard opens, it can be pushed below the visible drawer area instead of staying reachable in a fixed bottom action area.
   Proposed fix: convert DrawerContent to a flex column, move the scrollable content into `overflow-y-auto flex-1`, and render the submit button in a bottom bar outside the scroll area only when showOtherForm is true. Keep `disabled={isSendingHelp || !helpComment.trim()}` unchanged.
5. PM-135 / P2: openHelpDrawer() does not reset helpQuickSent, sendingCardId, showOtherForm, or helpComment before reopening. Because only closeHelpDrawer() resets them, a fast reopen can show stale success or stale form state.
   Proposed fix: reset `setHelpQuickSent(false)`, `setSendingCardId(null)`, `setShowOtherForm(false)`, and `setHelpComment('')` before `setIsHelpModalOpen(true)` and update the dependency array accordingly.
"@
codex exec $prompt

11. codex exec --help

